						<summary>

						<p>On a slab built into a platform of Viśvanātha temple.</p>						

						<p>Vīra-Ballāḷa II, 1212 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated the 22nd regnal year of the king, Āṅgirasa, Vaiśākha śu. 13, Sunday, corresponding to 1212 A.D., April 15.</p>						

						<p>It records a gift of gold to the god Madhusūdana by a <hi rend="italic">Seṭṭi</hi> in the presence of the One-Thousand <hi rend="italic">Mahājanas</hi> of Lokkiguṇḍi. Other details are not known, as the record is damaged.</p>						

						</summary>
